#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:51
msgid ""
"Note that you can still have widgets in rows within one column, and in "
"columns within one row. See the dashed lines in the images above. Similarly, "
"you can have widgets as tabs (see the yellow box in the screenshots above) "
"regardless of the dock orientation setting."
msgstr ""
"Merk op dat u nog steeds widgets in rijen kunt hebben binnen één kolom en in "
"kolommen in één rij. Zie de gestreepte lijnen in de bovenstaande "
"afbeeldingen. Evenzo kunt u widgets als tabbladen hebben (zie het gele vak "
"in de bovenstaande schermafdruk) ongeacht instelling van de oriëntatie van "
"de vastzetter."

#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:57
msgid "Adding Widgets"
msgstr "Widgets toevoegen"

#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:59
msgid ""
"You can add widgets (e.g. :ref:`view-library`, :ref:`view-project_notes`) by "
"enabling them in the :menuselection:`Menu --> View Menu`. Likewise, disable "
"them by taking off the check mark right next to their entry in the menu."
msgstr ""
"U kunt widgets toevoegen (bijv. :ref:`view-library`, :ref:`view-"
"project_notes`) door ze in te schakelen in :menuselection:`Menu --> Menu "
"bekijken`. Evenzo, schakel ze uit door deactivering rechts naast hun item in "
"het menu."

#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:65
msgid "Moving Widgets"
msgstr "Widgets verplaatsen"

#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:67
msgid ""
"You move a widget by grabbing the tab or the :term:`title bar` and moving it "
"to a new position. It is possible to move the widget to a different position "
"within the same panel thereby simply changing the sequence of the tabs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:69
msgid ""
"A widget can also be moved to a new panel, to its own (new) column or row, "
"or undocked as a floating window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_interface/customizing_interface.rst:71
msgid ""
"The Kdenlive layout reacts to your dragging of the widget and you need to "
"pay close attention which layout elements change color when you move over "
"them."
msgstr ""

